brief_summary.textblock:
To attest if a cardiac fatigue appears (and to measure it if it does) during intense physical exercises in two groups of subjects:
- Canoeists from a training center (Cesson-Sévigné) of the French canoeing team during an intensive session of three weeks of endurance training;
- Young recruits in military school of officers in ground forces of the French army (Saint-Cyr Coëtquidan) during an intensive.
